        "client_msg_id": "2ab5e01f-7747-4142-b259-2a92580fdad0",
        "text": "*The Cook and the Chef: Musk’s Secret Sauce*\n• #tags: #elon_musk #waitbutwhy #article #society #frame #narrative\n• \n• <https:\/\/waitbutwhy.com\/2015\/11\/the-cook-and-the-chef-musks-secret-sauce.html>\n• \n• brain as a computer and many other sloppy analogies\n• it seems at least at that time tim urban was kind of riding on the \"new atheists\" wave of the culture wars, has it informed his identity\n• the feedback loop patterns are interesting, but in the whole article he doesn't mention psychology?\n• quoting seth godin, I am reminded of jordan halls remark on him \n• musks \"reasoning from first principles\" its a frame of thought a view on the world see heideggers - aleteiha\n• but somehow it also could be look at everything with a fresh perspective - sadhguru\n• also it feels very strongly like the \"*naive progress story*\" daniel schmachtenberger mentions\n• \"musk software\" and grand theft life\n",
